parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the driver is unable to control the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when the brake pedal is applied
and may reach high speeds. The engine RPM may surge
and the vehicle may lurch forward or backward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can lead to unintended acceleration, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to disengage
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body or Idle Air Control Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the throttle body or idle air control valve can cause unintended acceleration, stalling, or difficulty controlling the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine RPM surges or drops unexpectedly
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates suddenly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, causing the vehicle to become unsafe to drive and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
leading to holes and weakening of the structure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spare tire assembly can cause the spare tire to fall off while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Spare tire holder rusted or broken
spare tire falls off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank strap can cause the fuel tank to fall off while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel tank strap rusted or broken
fuel tank falls off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Other structural issues, such as rusted shock mounts and bed rail supports, can lead to accidents or injuries.
Dashboard and interior issues, such as peeling silver coating, can cause distractions while driving and lead to accidents.
Warped front rotors can cause the brake pedal to vibrate or pulse, leading to reduced stopping power and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Vibration or pulsing of the brake pedal

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Accelerator Pedal Proximity
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake and accelerator pedals can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control.
Corrosion of the brake components can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the clutch and brake pedals can cause loss of control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Clutch and brake pedals fall to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause loss of control, leading to accidents.
